EUGENE Willard, a well-known defence attorney, is fighting for his life in hospital. The 34-year-old was shot at a mall in Heidedal kasi, Mangaung, over the weekend. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Among the cases Eugene was known for was the statutory rape case against gospel singer Sechaba Pali. Willard helped Pali avoid prison after he got a 15-year-old girl pregnant in 2012. Sechaba was given a suspended sentence of five years by the Ladybrand Magistrates Court in 2013.A cop, who did not want to be named, said Willard was shot three times while passing by the Lemo Mall on Tuesday night. “He was rushed to hospital, where he is fighting for his life in an ICU ward,” said the cop. A court official said she was shocked when she heard the news on Friday morning. “I have known Eugene for a very long time. He was full of jokes and very active at work but he later resigned and was no longer practising as a lawyer,” she said. When the SunTeam phoned Pali, he said it was the first he had heard of the shooting and he was very shocked. “I am glad he is still alive,” said the gospel singer. Police spokeswoman Sergeant Ikobeng Hlubi confirmed the incident and said the suspects were on the run. “The 34-year-old victim was walking near Lemo Mall at about 10pm. Two unknown men shot him three times in his chest and back before running away from the scene,” she said. “Heidedal cops are investigating a case of attempted murder but no arrests have been made. We urge anyone with information to contact Captain Malefetsane Khalienyane on 082 466 8387, 071 606 5715 or Crime Stop on 08600 10111.”